  "title" : "Hide inner classes as separate files in Project View in IntelliJ IDEA",
  "body" : "<p>I'm facing an issue with IntelliJ IDEA where it displays classes contained within a Java file as separate nodes in the Project View, rather than showing just the single .java file.</p>\n<p><strong>Problem:</strong>\nIn my Project panel, for a Java file that contains multiple classes, I see:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Main.java (file)\n<ul>\n<li>Learn (class contained in the file)</li>\n<li>Main (class contained in the file)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>What I want:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Just see &quot;Main.java&quot; as a single file entry</li>\n<li>Don't want to see the individual classes listed separately underneath</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/yMjGH70w.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/yMjGH70w.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n"
